  "prompt": "What are the questions asked in interviews?",
  "response": "Interview questions can vary widely depending on the industry, job role, and company. However, here are some common types of interview questions:\n\n1. Common General Questions:\n- Tell me about yourself\n- Why do you want to work here?\n- What are your strengths and weaknesses?\n- Where do you see yourself in 5 years?\n- What motivates you?\n\n2. Behavioral Questions:\n- Describe a challenging situation you've faced at work\n- Tell me about a time you demonstrated leadership\n- How do you handle conflicts?\n- Give an example of a successful team project\n- Describe a situation where you made a mistake\n\n3. Technical/Skill-Based Questions:\n- What skills do you have relevant to this role?\n- Can you explain [specific technical concept]?\n- What software/tools are you proficient in?\n- How do you stay updated with industry trends?\n\n4. Experience-Related Questions:\n- Walk me through your resume\n- Why did you leave your previous job?\n- What was your role in your last position?\n- What achievements are you most proud of?\n\n5. Company/Role-Specific Questions:\n- Why are you interested in this position?\n- What do you know about our company?\n- How would you contribute to our team?\n\nRemember, preparation and practicing responses can help you perform well in interviews.",
